						[[PNDS2]]


PNDS2 (Public Networking Data System 2) is a lightweight file storage and communication protocol built on top of HTTP and Flask.

The project began as a simple way to transfer files between devices and gradually evolved into a token-based storage system with ownership and permission management.

-------------<<Features>>

- Create public files
- Claim ownership of files
- Owner/Admin permission hierarchy
- Read, Write, and Append permissions
- Per-file token management
- Interactive command-line client
- HTTP-based architecture

Permission Model

Each claimed file contains:

- Owner Token
- Admin Token
- Read Token
- Write Token
- Append Token

Owner:

- Full control
- Can change admin token
- Can modify all permissions

Admin:

- Full access to file contents
- Can modify read/write/append permissions
- Cannot modify owner token
- Cannot modify admin token

Read Token:

- Grants read access

Write Token:

- Grants overwrite access

Append Token:

- Grants append access

------------<<Architecture>>

Storage:

files/

- file contents

tokens/

- permission metadata

Example:

main.py

main.py.tokens

The token file stores metadata such as:

{
	"owner": "...",
	"admin": "...",
	"r": "...",
	"w": "...",
	"a": "..."
}

Server Setup

Install dependencies:

pip install -r requirements.txt

Run:

python pnds_server2.py

Default server:

http://127.0.0.1:5000

Client Usage

Run:

python pnds2.py

Commands:

create <filename> <content>

read <filename>

append <filename> <content>

claim <filename> <owner_token>

modify <filename> <admin_token> <json>

list

tokens <filename> <token>

upload <localfile>

download <filename>

settoken <token>


-----------<<Motivation>>


The project was developed incrementally from a simple file transfer system. Each new requirement led to additional protocol layers:

File Transfer
→ Multiple Files
→ Session Management
→ Ownership
→ Token Permissions

PNDS2 is the result of that evolution.


-----------<<Future Ideas>>


- Folder support
- Virtual storage structures
- Messaging protocols
- Synchronization systems
- Distributed file routing
